B.Tn=new A.dK("Inconsistent spacing and visual hierarchy across screens","Card padding, heading sizes, and label styles varied across the dashboard, making it harder to scan quickly \u2014 a significant issue for practitioners working under time pressure.",B.cF,"Nielsen H4: Consistency and Standards","Standardised spacing tokens and type scale applied across all screens in the second iteration.")
B.Tm=new A.dK("Unclear copy on AI-enabled actions","Labels on AI-generated outputs did not make it obvious that the content was AI-produced, or that it required practitioner review before use.",B.cF,"Nielsen H1: Visibility of System Status","Explicit \u201cAI-generated \u2014 review before sending\u201d labels added to all AI outputs, with a distinct visual treatment separating them from practitioner-authored content.")
B.Ty=new A.dK("Weak visual affordance on interactive elements","Several action buttons and session cards did not communicate their interactivity clearly, leading the usability participant to hesitate before interacting.",B.dA,"Nielsen H7: Flexibility and Efficiency / 2.4.7 Focus Visible","Hover and focus states added. Primary actions given stronger visual weight with filled button styles.")
B.TA=new A.dK("No system feedback after voice commands","The initial voice assistant prototype gave no visible feedback that a command had been received or understood, leaving practitioners uncertain whether to repeat themselves.",B.dA,"Nielsen H1: Visibility of System Status","A brief animated confirmation state added between command input and checklist generation, confirming the assistant had processed the instruction.")
B.N9=s([B.Tn,B.Tm,B.Ty,B.TA],t.jW)
B.TB=new A.uR(B.a6,B.N9,"Accessibility and usability issues found","Issues surfaced during heuristic evaluation (Nielsen\u2019s ten heuristics) and addressed before practitioner testing.",null)
B.Tp=new A.dK("No progress indicator in a five-screen flow","People had no way to gauge how far through onboarding they were or how much was left, which fed straight into the sense that the effort was open-ended.",B.cF,"2.4.8 Location","Added a step indicator to every onboarding screen, showing current position and total steps.")
B.Tt=new A.dK("System permission dialogs appeared with no context","OS-level prompts for location and notifications arrived abruptly with no prior explanation. For anyone using a screen reader, the sudden modal shift was especially disorienting.",B.cF,"3.3.2 Labels or Instructions","Added a dedicated explainer screen before each OS prompt, with a plain-language reason and benefit for each permission requested.")
B.Ts=new A.dK("Avatar selection wasn\u2019t usable with VoiceOver or TalkBack","The initial avatar grid used tap targets that were too small and had no accessible labels, making selection hard for anyone navigating by touch or screen reader.",B.cF,"2.5.5 Target Size / 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value","Increased avatar tap targets to a minimum of 48x48dp and gave each one a semantic label describing the breed or character.")
B.Tu=new A.dK("Optional fields weren\u2019t labelled as optional","Photo upload and several profile fields were effectively optional but weren\u2019t marked as such, so people assumed they had to complete them to proceed.",B.dA,"3.3.2 Labels or Instructions","Labelled optional fields explicitly as \u201cOptional \u2014 you can add this later\u201d and added skip affordances where relevant.")
B.Tw=new A.dK("The feature carousel had no pause or manual control","The carousel auto-advanced on a timer with no way to pause or step through it, which is a problem for anyone who needs more time to read.",B.dA,"2.2.2 Pause, Stop, Hide","Made the carousel manually navigated by default, with swipe and dot-tap controls, and removed the auto-advance.")
